It wasn't the mother's or the American middle class whose voice was shouting anti-war rhetoric from our nation’s streets. It was violent, militant radical socialist voices with communist and radical socialist leaders that were shouting the loudest. When the American people turned them off they caused riots, mass demonstrations and began to burn the American flag and its corporate and government buildings. <br><br>
